22nd July 2015 ITV4
19:00 to 20:00 Stage 17 Highlights

Stage 17 is a carbon copy of stage 5 of the Dauphine from earlier this year - 161km from Digne-les-Bains to Pra Loup. It heads over the Col d'Allos which should act as a springboard for attacks before the final climb up to the finish. Bernard Thevenet won here in 1975, who will be the one to take his crown? Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary from Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting reporting at the roadside.
